2026 2026
1 which a juvenile court already has jurisdiction over the child to be
2 adopted under the Nebraska Juvenile Code, such juvenile court. Such
3 proceeding is considered a county court proceeding even if heard by a
4 juvenile court judge and an order of the juvenile court in such adoption
5 proceeding has the force and effect of a county court order. The
6 testimony in an adoption proceeding heard before a juvenile court judge
7 shall be preserved as in any other juvenile court proceeding.
8 (3) This section does not apply to the extent otherwise provided for
