15 to avail themselves of the services deemed necessary in the case plan or
16 permanency plan approved by the court if reasonable efforts to preserve
17 and reunify the family are required under section 43-283.01.
18 (4) Except as otherwise provided in the Nebraska Indian Child
19 Welfare Act, if a child is conceived by the victim of a sexual assault, a
20 petition for termination of parental rights of the perpetrator shall be
21 granted if such termination is in the best interests of the child and (a)
22 the perpetrator has been convicted of or pled guilty or nolo contendere
23 to sexual assault of the child’s birth parent under section 28-319 or
24 28-320 or a law in another jurisdiction similar to either section 28-319
25 or 28-320 or (b) the perpetrator has fathered the child or given birth to
26 the child as a result of such sexual assault.
27 (5) A petition for termination of parental rights is not required to
28 be filed on behalf of the state or, if a petition is filed, the state
29 shall not be required to join in the petition, if the juvenile is an
30 Indian child who may be eligible for a tribal customary adoption as
31 defined in section 43-1503.
